#[navbar]

#[section, $md:
    @../ (Documentation) / Aliases

    # Aliases

    Aliases give an existing thing a better name. They do not create a second value,
    a hidden conversion or a new nominal type.

    Beanstalk keeps `as` narrow: type names, imported names and arm-local payload
    captures.
]

